text: was a Japanese female professional wrestler. She wrestled for Stardom. Her mother is former wrestler Kyoko Kimura. Kimura was born in Yokohama, Japan. Kimura was trained at Wrestle-1's Professional Wrestling University. She debuted on March 30, 2016 against Reika Saiki in a losing effort for Wrestle-1. The pair wrestled against each many times throughout 2016 for Wrestle-1. Kimura killed herself by swallowing hydrogen sulfide on May 23, 2020, at the age of 22. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Drug-related suicides Category:Japanese professional wrestlers Category:Sportspeople from Yokohama
